I"|<p>Dubai internet is once again being an ass, so I’ll just link pictures for the moment….</p>

<p>Holy crap Dubai is crazy. The heat sucks, it’s in the middle of nowhere, and it has a bazillion awesome things to do. I don’t know how it works, and I don’t question it.</p>

<p>Flew in last night and even at about 10 or 11pm it was seriously close to 30 degrees. I quickly worked out my hotel that on the map looked way close to everything turned out to be close to nothing. Meh, whatever, the room was awesome and a touch of luxury after living in hostel dorms, and as it turns out the taxis are cheaper than chips… well, not if they’re chips with sauce and other condiments because I’m on a budget here, and those extras cut into that… Speaking of which, I had 2 servings of chips with cheesy/nacho type sauce all over them today. Ok, so I can afford that, but yeh, the taxis are cheap so today I’ve pretty much been chauffered around the place.</p>

<p>In the morning I started off at The Mall of The Emirates where I was way keen to hit the slopes (swear I’m not being racist, Simon) and go for a bit of a snowboard session. 2 hours for about $60-80, including all rentals and whatnot. Was awesome fun, but I was well knackered after it.</p>

<p><a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2160.jpg">The snow park</a><br />
<a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2161.jpg">View from the top of the run</a><br />
