<a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2163.jpg">View from the bottom of the run</a></p>

<p>After a little shopping, I moved on to Atlantis, which is that hotel at the top of that palm-shaped island. Drove past the Al Arab hotel (that 7-star hotel) on the way. The taxi driver offered to take a photo of me in front of it. So look at that first picture:<br />
<a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2167.jpg">The Al Arab</a></p>

<p>Ok, now here’s the one the cabbie took of me.<br />
<a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2169.jpg">Me</a></p>

<p>So go back to that first picture, and now pretend I’m standing in front of that hotel. That’s what it’s <em>supposed</em> to look like, and when it’s that huge I’m really not sure how he missed getting it in the frame. You might be able to tell I started pissing myself laughing at this point, not sure he knew what was going on…</p>

<p>Anyway Atlantis was ok, I went walking around an aquarium which looked really cool…<br />
