<a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2204.jpg">Sunset outside Atlantis</a></p>

<p>After all this I made my way to Dubai Mall, the world’s biggest (I think), right next to the world’s tallest building, the Burj Khalifa. As soon as I saw it my initial reaction was kinda like Homer’s after receiving the giant Foster’s can – “Yeh, I guess it’s pretty big.” It’s obviously large, but it’s not really all that impressive… well not from the street anyway. There’s tons of super-high-rise buildings around so it’s kinda like looking at a 7′ tall guy in a room full of people 6’6″…</p>

<p><a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2207.jpg">The Burj Khalifa</a><br />
<a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/europe%202010/IMG_2216.jpg">They had a Belaggio-esque water display go off in the fountain outside</a></p>

<p>Back to the mall for a second… this place was so big I literally got lost in it. Insane. Took me about 3 hours to walk through the whole thing, and funnily enough there was seriously maybe 5 or 6 shops I really looked at. Picked up a few things and managed to burn through most of the rest of my cash. Good times.</p>

<p>Dubai, you’ve been rad. I shall see you again!</p>
